## Step 2: Set up batch inference (optional)

Your inference notebook (`{{ inference_notebook }}`) should:
1. Load the champion model from Unity Catalog
2. Score a table and write predictions

```python
import mlflow

model_name = dbutils.widgets.get("model_name")
model = mlflow.pyfunc.load_model(f"models:/{model_name}@champion")

input_table = dbutils.widgets.get("input_table_name")
output_table = dbutils.widgets.get("output_table_name")

df = spark.table(input_table)
predictions = model.predict(df.toPandas())
spark.createDataFrame(predictions).write.mode("overwrite").saveAsTable(output_table)
```

